title: U.S. apparel trade group calls to recall Canadian Parliament as ports strike enters 10th day
description: Trade associations both in the United States and Canada warn the impact will inflate prices and cause weeks of delays in product arrivals.

title: The American banking landscape is on the cusp of a seismic shift. Expect more pain to come
description: What is coming will likely be the most significant shift in the American banking landscape since the 2008 financial crisis. Bank earnings kick off Friday.

title: PGA Tour defends LIV Golf deal ahead of Senate hearing
description: The PGA Tour defended its proposed deal with LIV Golf, while its board goes through a shake-up with the resignation of former AT&T chief Randall Stephenson.

title: Britain to unleash $64 billion in pension funding for tech startups after missing out on Arm IPO
description: The U.K. announced an agreement with the country's largest defined contribution pension schemes to allocate 5% of assets to unlisted equities by 2030.

title: Apple supplier Foxconn pulls out of $19.5 billion India chip project
description: Foxconn said the decision was by "mutual agreement," but that it remained "confident" about India's semiconductor ambitions.

title: Lithuania says on eve of NATO summit that providing Ukraine with a pathway to membership is an 'achievable goal'
description: Lithuania's president said Monday that establishing a pathway for Ukraine's fully fledged NATO membership at this week's summit was an "achievable goal."

title: Now Boarding: Why is boarding an airplane so difficult?
description: On this episode of "Now Boarding," CNBC discusses why boarding an airplane takes so long and what airlines are doing to change it.

title: Bearer of rare 'One Ring' card from 'Lord of the Rings' lore could fetch $2 million and face hefty tax bill
description: An ultra-rare "One Ring" serialized "Magic: The Gathering" card was reportedly found by an individual in Canada. If sold, they'd likely owe a big tax on profits.

title: European regulator to review weight-loss drugs following reports of suicidal thoughts
description: Danish firm Novo Nordisk says "patient safety is a top priority" following reports.

title: Twitter traffic is 'tanking' as Meta's Threads hits 100 million users
description: User traffic on Twitter has slowed since the launch of Threads, which has already surpassed 100 million sign-ups since its debut last week.

title: Yellen's latest trip helps set a new normal for the U.S.-China relationship
description: U.S. Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen has become the second U.S. cabinet member to visit China in a month, setting the stage for more high-level communication.

title: This is 'the end of the beginning' of the battle against inflation, economist says
description: Top Societe Generale economist Kokou Agbo-Bloua said: "The central banks need to trigger a recession ... but we're not there yet."

title: Biden advisor defends stimulus and inflation surge: 'The real cause was the global pandemic'
description: Heather Boushey is a member of President Joe Biden's Council of Economic Advisers.

title: Dutch PM Mark Rutte says he won't run for fifth term after government collapses
description: Dutch Prime Minister Mark Rutte announced on Monday that he won't run for a fifth term in office.

title: Sweden is in the final stretch to NATO membership. But Turkey could yet derail it
description: NATO is convening in Vilnius to approve new defense plans, and — its leaders hope — announce the full approval of Sweden to the alliance.

title: Goldman Sachs says India will overtake the U.S. to become the world's second-largest economy by 2075
description: India is poised to become the world's second largest economy by 2075, overtaking the U.S., Japan and Germany, Goldman Sachs forecasts.

title: Alibaba shares rise after Chinese regulators fine Ant Group, ending regulatory uncertainty
description: Alibaba's Hong Kong-listed shares rose 4% in Monday morning trade amid hopes of the years-long scrutiny of its financial arm Ant Group coming to an end.

title: China's producer prices sink again in June in latest sign of struggling economic recovery
description: China's producer prices sank more than expected, official data showed Monday, underscoring the challenges for the country in revitalizing growth momentum.

title: CNBC Daily Open: June’s jobs report won’t deter Fed from hikes
description: There were 50,000 fewer jobs than forecast in June. But that's not enough for the Federal Reserve to hold interest rates steady at its upcoming meeting.

title: China's consumer-driven sectors are a 'sweet spot' and opportunity for investors, says KKR
description: From pet food to liquor and lighting fixtures, global investing company KKR is putting their money behind a suite of consumer-driven sectors in China.
